  {
    "channel_id": "chan-001",
    "content": "Quick question on the runbook: when a node goes NotReady, do we cordon before or after draining?",
    "content_type": "text",
    "created_date": "2026-06-25T18:02:14.000Z",
    "from_display_name": "Blake Kim",
    "from_user_id": "user-005",
    "id": "msg-00167",
    "importance": "normal",
    "team_id": "19:team-0001@thread.tacv2"
  },
  {
    "channel_id": "chan-001",
    "content": "Cordon first, always. It stops new pods landing on a node you're about to drain. Then drain, then investigate.",
    "content_type": "text",
    "created_date": "2026-06-25T18:09:50.000Z",
    "from_display_name": "Corey Holloway",
    "from_user_id": "user-001",
    "id": "msg-0020a",
    "importance": "normal",
    "team_id": "19:team-0001@thread.tacv2"
  },
  {
    "channel_id": "chan-001",
    "content": "Makes sense. And if the drain hangs on a pod that won't evict?",
    "content_type": "text",
    "created_date": "2026-06-25T18:15:27.000Z",
    "from_display_name": "Blake Kim",
    "from_user_id": "user-005",
    "id": "msg-00360",
    "importance": "normal",
    "team_id": "19:team-0001@thread.tacv2"
  },
  {
    "channel_id": "chan-001",
    "content": "Check for a PodDisruptionBudget blocking it. Nine times out of ten that's the culprit. Don't force-delete unless you understand why it's stuck.",
    "content_type": "text",
    "created_date": "2026-06-25T18:22:41.000Z",
    "from_display_name": "Corey Holloway",
    "from_user_id": "user-001",
    "id": "msg-004b6",
    "importance": "normal",
    "team_id": "19:team-0001@thread.tacv2"
  },
  {
